cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper analyzes a large corpus of publicly available data files on the internet and studies the file size distribution for several distinct data types. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories, as it deals with the analysis of large data sets and their distribution. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of real-world economic constraints on the growth of globally stored information, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the distribution of multimedia files, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
